# Start with peace, not intensity

Many people think change begins with a dramatic push.

Most of the time, it begins with a calmer pace and a few repeated decisions that keep the body from living in constant stress.

## Five rhythms worth practicing

1. Eat familiar meals during busy weeks instead of reinventing everything.
2. Go outside and walk, even if the walk is short.
3. Choose one realistic bedtime and defend it.
4. Pause before saying yes to commitments that will steal peace.
5. Return to Scripture before returning to panic.

## Simplicity is not weakness

Simple routines often look unimpressive from the outside, but they are powerful because they can be repeated.

The goal is not to perform. The goal is to build a life that is stable enough to obey with joy.
